{"id":118028,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bright%27s_disease","text":"Bright's disease is a historical classification of kidney diseases that are now called acute or chronic nephritis. The main symptom is the presence of serum albumin (blood plasma protein) in the urine, and frequently accompanied by oedema and hypertension.\nThe term is no longer used, as the disease is now classified by its better known causes.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"History","surface_form":"historical","offset":22},{"uri":"Scientific_classification","surface_form":"classification","offset":33},{"uri":"Kidney","surface_form":"kidney","offset":51},{"uri":"Diseases","surface_form":"diseases","offset":58},{"uri":"Acute_(medicine)","surface_form":"acute","offset":87},{"uri":"Chronic","surface_form":"chronic","offset":96},{"uri":"Nephritis","surface_form":"nephritis","offset":104},{"uri":"Symptom","surface_form":"symptom","offset":124},{"uri":"Blood_plasma","surface_form":"blood plasma","offset":166},{"uri":"Urine","surface_form":"urine","offset":195},{"uri":"Oedema","surface_form":"oedema","offset":232},{"uri":"Hypertension","surface_form":"hypertension","offset":243}]}